      • getTarget

        public String getTarget()
        Gets the current script target. This may return null if the script is not set to execute on a target. This only updates immediately preceding a script's execution.
        Returns:
        The current script target or null.

      • setScriptFolder

        public void setScriptFolder(File folder)

        Parameters:
        folder - The new folder that said scripts should launch from.

      • stringReplace

        public String stringReplace(String string)
        Loops through all StringReplacers registered with this Buscript object and replaces their regex strings with their replacement string and returns the result. By default this includes a replacement of %t with the script's current target. This will also replace '&' with the appropriate color character. Note: This ONLY works correctly when used from within a script function.
        Parameters:
        string - The string to replace in.
        Returns:
        The string that has had replacements for each registered StringReplacer.

      • registerStringReplacer

        public void registerStringReplacer(StringReplacer replacer)
        Adds a new StringReplacer to this Buscript instance which will allow built in global script functions to replace strings as defined by the replacer.
        Parameters:
        replacer - the new StringReplacer to add.

      • addScriptMethods

        public void addScriptMethods(Object obj)
        Adds all methods from the given obj to the global scope. Methods intended to be added should all have unique names or you may have conflicts.
        Parameters:
        obj - The object whose methods should be added.

      • getScriptVariable

        public <T> T getScriptVariable(String name,
                               Class<T> type)
        Obtains the value of a global scope variable that will be automatically casted to the type parameter.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type represented by the type parameter.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the javascript "var" to obtain.
        type - A class representing the type to cast the variable's value to.
        Returns:
        The value of of variable, automatically cast to the given type. If unable to cast or value is null, null will be returned.

      • runScriptFunction

        public Object runScriptFunction(Object obj,
                                String functionName,
                                Object... args)
                         throws FunctionNotFoundException,
                                ScriptException
        Executes a javascript function. The function must be declared in the scripting environment before this is called.
        Parameters:
        obj - - "Scope" object for use as the 'this' object in javascript.
        functionName - The name of the javascript function.
        args - - Arguments for the script function.
        Returns:
        The result of the function call.
        Throws:
        ScriptException - if the calling of the function resulted in an exception.
        FunctionNotFoundException - if the named variable is not a function or its value is null.

      • clearScriptCache

        public void clearScriptCache()
        Clears scripts that have been cached so that they may be reloaded from the disk. Scripts are typically cached when set bound to an event.
